The article discusses President Obama's plan to raise the minimum wage for federal contract workers to $10.10 per hour through an executive order. The President also calls on Congress to pass the Harkin-Miller bill, which would increase the federal minimum wage for all workers. The article emphasizes that raising the minimum wage will benefit hardworking Americans, improve productivity, and reduce turnover. It also mentions that businesses like Costco support increasing the minimum wage because it helps build a strong workforce and profitability. The article highlights that the current minimum wage has not kept up with inflation and that indexing it to inflation would help lower-income workers. It also mentions that raising the minimum wage would particularly benefit women and parents. The article concludes by stating that Americans across the country are in support of raising the minimum wage.